headline: What The Shifting Story Means For TD SYNNEX's Valuation Outlook
summary: TD SYNNEX’s fair value estimate has been nudged up from about US$178.27 to about US$179.73, even as the model now applies a slightly higher discount rate of about 9.49% and a more cautious revenue growth outlook of about 4.10% versus about 4.92% before. This mix of a modestly higher fair value with a tougher hurdle rate reflects how analysts are weighing enthusiasm around expected FY26 billings and higher value segments against concerns raised on memory pricing and demand elasticity.
